";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"frank\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1495:\"<p>if “Load WebP or AVIF in supported browsers?” is on, <code>.png</code> files with transparency will loose that transparency in browsers that support AVIF due to a recent technical change in Shortpixel’s AVIF toolchain.</p>\n<p>Shortpixel is looking at alternative solutions, but until then as a workaround you can either:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>add <code>.png</code> to Autoptimize’s lazyload exclusion field</li>\n<li>or to use below code snippet to disable AVIF images;</li>\n</ul>\n<p><code>add_filter( \'autoptimize_filter_imgopt_do_avif\', \'__return_false\');</code></p>\n<div class=\'yarpp-related-rss\'>\n<p>Possibly related twitterless twaddle:<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://blog.futtta.be/2020/10/09/autoptimize-with-support-for-avif-images/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Autoptimize with support for AVIF images\">Autoptimize with support for AVIF images </a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://blog.futtta.be/2018/05/24/autoptimize-2-4-beta-3-includes-image-optimization/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Autoptimize 2.4 beta 3 includes image optimization!\">Autoptimize 2.4 beta 3 includes image optimization! </a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://blog.futtta.be/2020/09/15/want-to-test-avif-images-with-autoptimizes-image-optimization/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Want to test AVIF images with Autoptimize&#8217;s Image Optimization?\">Want to test AVIF images with Autoptimize&#8217;s Image Optimization? </a></li>\n</ul></p>\n</div>\n<img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/futtta_autoptimize/~4/OzcZU5FJxgg\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\" alt=\"\"/>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8: